Description: Shell of a marine bivalve mollusc of the 'Unis Teretrusculus' species.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Town (Naukratis), probably example found near the river by Petrie (Petrie Journal 1884-5, 186) (probably)
Curator's comments: Found in box of unregistered shells with other shells that had handwritten slips written by Petrie identifying the shell species and naming Naukratis as the provenance. This shell was found with a note by Petrie: 'Unis teretrusculus Nile Nebireh (Naucratis) 1885'.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (WC.12)
